Change has been successfully merged
Looks like the CI unit-test.py forces meson projects to use `-Dwerror=true` and `-Dwarning_level=3`, which fails the build. So I will fix all the warnings in new commits underneath this one.

Usually you want to ignore `build*/`.
Usually you don't want to ignore the .wrap files.
Done. `/subprojects/*/` only ignores the auto-generated directories and not the .wrap files.
Might as well set this to c++23 since almost all the other repos are on that now, right?
Done
Does this make a noticeable difference?  My opinion is we should try to reduce the repo-level customization.
By my simple comparison, it saves about 3.5% on binary size (8 KiB for `smbiosmdrv2app`). I will opt to keep RTTI disabled for now.
nit, these are generally of type "feature" rather than boolean.  Not required to be fixed, but consistency is good.
Done

Not required, but consider formatting this file similar to:
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/meson_options.txt

with line options in indented blocks, which makes it a lot more readable in review, and doesn't end up with lines larger than the coding standard (80)
Done
I learned something new.  I think all our ipmi meson files could use this instead of shared_library and then eliminate the `b_lundef=false`.
One difference is that it generates unversioned .so files, which Yocto (and maybe other tools) don't expect. But I agree it's probably the right tool for plugin-style shared libraries.
Oh.  Hmm.  Isn't that going to be problematic from the automatic package creation of debug packages, etc?

I'm not sure what the implications are, since I have never used -dev or -dbg packages. I did have to change the `FILES` pattern in the recipe since `${SOLIBS}` only pulls in versioned libs: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/65472
nit: `allowed` and not `enabled` (change throughout).
Done
